content.text: Pneumatic differential calculus is an advanced mathematical framework for modeling gas dynamics in non-equilibrium thermodynamic systems, incorporating Boltzmann transport coefficients and modified Navier-Stokes approximations for rarefied gas regimes characterized by parameters like the Knudsen number and Chapman-Enskog velocity distribution expansions.
